## 📱 Flutter Rules

### Structure (feature-first)
```
lib/features/<feature>/
├── screens/
├── widgets/
├── models/
└── providers/
```

### Mandatory Patterns
- Dio for ALL HTTP — NEVER the http package
- All models: fromJson(Map<String, dynamic>) + toJson()
- Riverpod for ALL state management
- setState only for purely local UI (e.g. show/hide password)
- JWT in flutter_secure_storage — NEVER SharedPreferences
- go_router for ALL navigation — NEVER Navigator.push
- Always handle 3 states: loading / error / data
- Never hardcode colors, fonts, or sizes — always use theme
- All API base URLs from core/api/api_client.dart
- All endpoints as constants in core/api/endpoints.dart

### UI Rules (CRITICAL)
The UI must be:
- Clean, modern, and visually polished
- Interactive with smooth animations and transitions
- Dynamic — real data, real states, nothing static
- NOT generic AI-looking (no plain white lists, no boring forms)
- Consistent design system: one color palette, one font family
- Use cards, gradients, icons, and visual hierarchy
- Every screen must feel like a real product, not a prototype

### Design System
Define once in core/theme/:
- Primary color: deep blue (#1E3A5F)
- Accent color: electric blue (#2E86C1)
- Background: dark or light (decide at start, stick with it)
- Font: Inter or Poppins (Google Fonts)
- Border radius: 12px standard, 20px for cards
- Consistent spacing scale: 8, 16, 24, 32px

